issue.title: fetch should deliver all current matches
issue.body: When registering a new fetch, all current matches should be notified to the registering peer before sending the response of the register request.

issue.title: exception on EPIPE
issue.body:
I experienced the following exception:

events.js:72
        throw er; // Unhandled 'error' event
              ^
Error: write EPIPE
    at errnoException (net.js:901:11)
    at Object.afterWrite (net.js:718:19)

IN my opinion node-jet should close the connection to the "offending" peer and proceed.
